article.headline: Houston 82, Tulane 57
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Oliver Lafayette scored 19 points to lead Houston to a 82-57 victory over Tulane Wednesday. Houston (11-6, 2-3 Conference USA) drained 60 percent of its shots in the first half (21-of-58) and the defense limited the Green Wave (5-12, 1-4) to 20 second-half points. Lafayette scored five of Houston's 14 3-pointers. Brian Latham added 18 points for the Cougars, Ramon Dyer had 14 and Lanny Smith had 11. Matt Wheaton led Tulane with 11 points. Houston went into halftime with a 22-point lead, and scored the first seven points of the second half for the biggest lead at 67-37 with 16:47 left to play.
